Rivers State Governor, Nyesom Ezenwo Wike and General Overseer of Mountain of Fire and Miracles Ministries Worldwide, Dr. Daniel Olukoya, will on Friday, December 13, 2019, witness the commissioning and dedication of 14,000-seating capacity auditorium of the MFM Church in Rumuola, Port Harcourt. Also expected at the dedication of the auditorium tagged; ‘The Tabernacle of God’, are leaders of the Christian Association of Nigeria (CAN) and the Penticostal Fellowship of Nigeria (PFN). The MFM, in a statement issued in Port Harcourt , said the auditorium was built and equipped by the South-South 1 Region of the Church. The statement, which was signed by the Principal Regional Overseer, Pastor Lawrence Olasehinde, and the Chairman, Media Committee, Pastor Chinedu Udechukwu, the MFM General Overseer will also commission new church auditoria built in Eleme, Port Harcourt Township and Ozuoba on Thursday, December 12, 2019 It said there will be a special deliverance and Manna Water service by 7:00am on Saturday, December 14 and a special thanksgiving service, which would commence at 7:30am, on Sunday, December 15, 2019. The statement invites the general public to this special programme, which would usher in salvation, healing, restoration, breakthroughs and great deliverance.